        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(plugin-sdk): generic outbound delivery-report seam; WhatsApp native auto-reply reports provider-accepted sends",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nChannel-self-delivered sends (native auto-replies) bypass core `deliverOutboundPayloads`, so the canonical `message:sent` event never fires and `message:sent` consumers (the `message_sent` plugin hook + the internal `message:sent` hook) are blind to them despite successful delivery. Today there is no extension-facing way to report such a delivery (`emitMessageSent`/`createInternalHookEvent`/`getGlobalHookRunner` are core-internal).\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nCore owns the canonical `message.sent` emission; extensions need a narrow, generic, supported way to report a delivery they performed without reaching into core hook internals. This adds one shared core emitter (`emitCanonicalMessageSent`) that both the explicit-send path and the new seam route through, so the two emission sites cannot drift in hook order or gating.\n\n## User Impact\nPlugins/consumers observing `message_sent` / internal `message:sent` now also observe channel-self-delivered messages (e.g. delivery logs, responded-accounting, watchdogs). The explicit-send path is unchanged. Additive and fail-open — no change to delivery behavior or config.\n\n## Evidence\nNew `src/infra/outbound/report-outbound-delivered.test.ts` (Vitest): emits exactly one canonical `message:sent`; idempotent on `messageId` / `channel`+`to`+`correlationId`; fails open (no throw, internal hook skipped) when `sessionKey` is absent; never throws when a downstream hook handler throws. The `deliver.ts` refactor is behavior-preserving (delegates to the shared emitter; removes the now-duplicated emission). Touched files typecheck clean locally (scoped); deferring to CI/tsgo for the authoritative run.\n\nCloses #97726\n\n### Proof status\nCovered by the new unit test (`report-outbound-delivered.test.ts`) exercising the real internal-hook path. A redacted live-WhatsApp capture is not included because the contributor has no spare WhatsApp number and will not pair the production number; a maintainer-run Mantis visual proof would be the authoritative real-transport check. The plugin-sdk surface budgets were updated for the one new subpath (+1 entrypoint, +2 exports, +1 callable).",
